LogFile.FinalText: Some claim that men and women speak different languages. If a man in a relationship says that he doesn't want to talk about his problems, the typical woman will feel excluded from his world. If the woman says to him that she doesn't want to talk about the problems, most men believe that she doesn't need to talk about them. Such misunderstandings lead to fights. When the big fights come along, women and men also react in different ways. New research shows that many women cry when they are angry. In those situations the frightened men choose to run away, and they may feel helpless. In contrast to the crying woman, the angry man uses harsh words. Despite these different reactions, most men and women manage to live together in peach - and we probably cannot live without each other!
